ğŸ“Œ Project Overview

Credit card fraud is a major challenge in the financial sector, causing significant losses every year. Detecting fraudulent transactions quickly and accurately is essential to protect users and financial institutions.
This project implements a Credit Card Fraud Detection system using machine learning to classify transactions as Fraudulent or Legitimate based on transaction features.

The model is designed to handle highly imbalanced data, a common characteristic of fraud detection problems.

